---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="about">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About Me</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    <p class="mb-4">
      I have a broad interest in <b>AI</b>, <b>HCI</b>, and <b>Psychology</b>.
      My ultimate goal is to pursue research that is necessary yet underexplored.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Recently, I've been interested in how well the mental models of AI and humans are aligned,
      and whether this alignment can help us better understand autism.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 1 -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">What Do We Live For</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    <p class="mb-4">
      The world is full of suffering. Cruelty wounds others, and our own flaws inevitably hurt those around us.
      Even in the absence of malice, we spend our lives in constant tension — building walls, seeking safety,
      and bracing ourselves against uncertainty.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      I often wonder: if life is so fragile and pain so pervasive, what makes it worth living?
      I believe the answer lies in choosing to face that suffering — not by looking away, but by working toward
      something that eases the burden for others, even just a little.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 2 -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Why I Do Research</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    <p class="mb-4">
      Some people in this world experience it in ways most of us never fully understand.
      Whether due to cognitive differences, social barriers, or simply being overlooked,
      there are those who struggle to connect, communicate, or be understood.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      I do research because I want to bridge that gap. By studying how AI and humans align in their understanding
      of the world, I hope to uncover insights that help us better support those who think and perceive differently —
      particularly individuals on the autism spectrum. Research, to me, is not just an academic pursuit;
      it is a way to advocate for the underexplored and the unheard.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 3 -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Beyond Research</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    <p class="mb-4">
      Outside of my academic life, I find meaning and joy in a few things that keep me grounded:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
      <li><b>CCC & Discipleship</b> — I'm actively involved in CCC (Cru) and discipleship training, where I grow in faith and community.</li>
      <li><b>Music</b> — I play instruments as a way to express myself and unwind. Music has always been a constant companion.</li>
      <li><b>Gaming</b> — Games are where I recharge. Whether it's strategic thinking or just having fun, gaming is my go-to break.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
